parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the motorized seat belt can cause the belt to malfunction, leading to inadequate restraint in the event of an accident, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt fails to retract
the seat belt retracts back and forth without being occupied
the seat belt locks up
the seat belt fails to retract as designed
the seat belt does not return to its starting position.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt track cable can cause the seat belt to malfunction, leading to inadequate restraint in the event of an accident, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt track cable is broken.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Incomplete recall repairs can lead to continued malfunction of the seat belt system, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: Recall work not completed due to problems with the dealer and schedule.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Seat Belt Failure After Recall Repairs

symptoms: The seat belt failed after recall repairs
causing a passenger to be hit in the head.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Design Flaw in Motorized Seat Belts
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design flaw in motorized seat belts can cause drivers and passengers to forget to fasten their lap belts, leading to inadequate restraint in the event of an accident, which can increase the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The automatic motor belt design causes drivers and passengers to forget to fasten their lap belts.

symptoms: The sliding door comes off the track

the door is difficult to open or close.
